<div id="review_1235033738" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1235033738" />
    <a title="Rachel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8587420-rachel"><img alt="Rachel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1474725481p2/8587420.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1235033738?book_show_action=true">Mar 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rachel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rachel" href="/user/show/8587420-rachel">Rachel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1235033738" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12462523463101934255">&apos;Deception on Sable Hill&apos; is the second in the Chicago World&apos;s Fair Mystery series by Shelley Gray. I loved the first book &apos;Secrets of Sloane House&apos; and this book picks up nicely. A society slasher is on the loose in Chicago attacking ladies of the upper class and slashing their faces, sometimes murdering them. Eloisa Carstairs meets the handsome Detective Sean Ryan at a party and even though she is upper class and he is working class and Irish, a friendship begins. And Sean&apos;s partner, Owen Howa</span>
  <span id="freeText12462523463101934255" style="display:none">'Deception on Sable Hill' is the second in the Chicago World's Fair Mystery series by Shelley Gray. I loved the first book 'Secrets of Sloane House' and this book picks up nicely. A society slasher is on the loose in Chicago attacking ladies of the upper class and slashing their faces, sometimes murdering them. Eloisa Carstairs meets the handsome Detective Sean Ryan at a party and even though she is upper class and he is working class and Irish, a friendship begins. And Sean's partner, Owen Howard, himself an aristocrat, falls for Sean's sister Katie. The mores of society at the time and the distinction of classes is examined and we can slowly see it begin to break down. Both Eloisa and Sean question the validity of the class system and both explore opportunities to rise above it. An engaging mystery from start to finish with likable characters and the struggles they are dealing with, I thoroughly enjoyed this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12462523463101934255" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


